name: $50 Grab Bag
description: FIFTY DOLLARS OF RANDOM AWESOME ZINES Do you remember going to the showground and scouring the showbag halls for the perfect combination of lollies, chocolate and toys in the perfect showbag? Well, here at Bird in the Hand, we spent all of our show money on showbags. The rides weren't for us. Now that we've got all these wondrous zines in our shop, we want to share them with you and the best way for you to get a taste of what we have to offer is by snapping up one of these grab bags. You'll get a random mix of at least fifty dollars worth of zines from around Australia and the world. You'll also get some 'You' or other free zines we have available. You don't even need to leave your couch (or work desk...sneaky sneaky!).

name: Voiceworks Grab Bags
description:
This month we're celebrating Australian publication Voiceworks by offering grab bags of back-issues.  

You'll get 5 back-issues of Voiceworks for $15.00 <FONT COLOR=RED>(INCLUDING POSTAGE!!!)</FONT>

Voiceworks is a national, quarterly magazine that features exciting new writing by Australian young writers. It is a unique opportunity for young writers and artists (under 25) to publish their poetry, short stories, articles and comics, illustrations, drawings and photos, as well as receiving feedback on their submission. It is produced entirely by young people and relies totally on contributions from the readers to make up the content. 

The magazine is produced by the editor together with a group of interns and a volunteer editorial committee (EdComm), all of whom are under 25. EdComm assists the editor in reading submissions, editing content, proofreading, running launches, and writing feedback for all our contributors.
